    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2017-04-25</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon request, to extend for up to six years the time period during which construction must commence on the Jennings Randolph Hydroelectric Project located on the North Branch of the Potomac River in Garrett County, Maryland, and Mineral County, West Virginia.</p> <p>Additionally, FERC may reinstate the construction license if it is expired.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-06-28T15:43:34Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2017-04-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Passed House without amendment</actionDesc>
          <name>Passed House without amendment</name>
          <versionCode>81</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2017-06-12</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</p> <p>(Sec.1)This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon request, to extend for up to six years the time period during which construction must commence on the Jennings Randolph Hydroelectric Project located on the North Branch of the Potomac River in Garrett County, Maryland, and Mineral County, West Virginia.</p> <p>Additionally, FERC may reinstate the construction license if it is expired.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-10-13T11:57:56Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2017-06-12T15:27:23Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
